OL,3,CReeves' enormous budget should perhaps
OL,4,Chave been bigger still
OL,6,FITV News' Political Editor Robert
OL,7,FPeston spoke to the Chancellor about
OL,8,Fher Budget, questioning her on the
OL,9,FOBR's prediction that GDP will be no
OL,10,Fhigher at the end of this parliament,
OL,11,Fdespite the new measures
OL,13,FThe sums of money raised by Rachel
OL,14,FReeves in tax and borrowed, and then
OL,15,Fspent and invested, are breathtakingly
OL,16,Flarge.
OL,18,FPublic expenditure is set to rise by
OL,19,F#70bn a year, with two thirds going on
OL,20,Fday-to-day spending and one third on
OL,21,Finvestment.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
