OL,3,CReeves' enormous budget should perhaps
OL,4,Chave been bigger still
OL,6,FHigher taxes will raise #36bn a year,
OL,7,Fincreasing the share of the economy
OL,8,Ftaken in taxes to a record 38% by the
OL,9,Fend of the parliament.
OL,11,FBorrowing is set to rise by #32bn a
OL,12,Fyear, and - as the OBR says - the
OL,13,Fnational debt in underlying terms is
OL,14,Fset to rise every year for five years.
OL,16,FSo surely - you might argue - with
OL,17,Fsuch ambition shown by Rachel Reeves
OL,18,Fthe UK will see public services fixed
OL,19,Fand investment rise to the extent that
OL,20,Fproductivity and economic growth must
OL,21,Fsurely recover at last.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
