OL,3,CReeves' enormous budget should perhaps
OL,4,Chave been bigger still
OL,6,FSecond, the choice of employers'
OL,7,Fnational insurance as the main tax
OL,8,Fraising measure - extracting #25bn
OL,9,Ffrom companies - combined with the
OL,10,Ffiscal loosening, the increased
OL,11,Fgovernment borrowing, actually lead to
OL,12,Flower private-sector investment,
OL,13,Faccording to the Office for Budget
OL,14,FResponsibility.
OL,16,FThis is particularly embarrassing for
OL,17,Fa prime minister who repeatedly said
OL,18,Fduring the general election that he
OL,19,Fwanted businesses to invest much more,
OL,20,Fto revive the country's prosperity.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
